cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with transfer learning for visual content classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes methods to improve the universality of the CNN-based representation of images, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of annotated data and proposes methods to limit the need for it, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new evaluation protocol for comparing the ability of CNN-based representation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL - Computation and Language) and multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia).
